modules.description: Initializes a configuration object from a file path, loading and parsing its contents. Works with a structured record type containing settings and parameters. Used to set up application defaults and environment-specific values during startup.

Provides geolocation data for IP addresses by querying a configured service, returning a status code and parsed JSON response. Works with IP strings, configuration records, and Yojson data structures. Used to determine country and network information for user IP addresses during access control checks.

Provides domain information extraction and WHOIS lookup capabilities. Operates on strings representing domain names and returns parsed WHOIS data along with status codes. Enables retrieval of domain name and extension components from raw domain strings.

Provides IP and domain-based geolocation and network data retrieval, including location details, time zones, ISP, weather stations, and ASN. Processes IPv4 and IPv6 addresses along with domain names to return structured records with fields like latitude, longitude, ZIP code, and WHOIS information. Enables integration with external APIs to fetch real-time network and domain metadata for applications requiring location-aware services or network diagnostics.

Loads configuration from a file and uses it to query geolocation data for IP addresses, returning structured results including country and network details. Processes domain names to extract components and perform WHOIS lookups, yielding parsed domain and registration information. Operates on configuration records, IP strings, domain strings, and JSON data, enabling environment setup, access control, and domain analysis. Supports tasks such as determining user origin by IP and parsing domain registration metadata.
